#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:5
msgid "QGIS Coding Standards"
msgstr "QGIS standardi kodiranja"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:10
msgid ""
"QGIS coding standards are described in the policy document available at `QEP"
" #314 <https://github.com/qgis/QGIS-Enhancement-"
"Proposals/blob/master/qep-314-coding-style.md>`_. All developers are "
"required to follow those policies. Please note that QEP #314 is a live "
"document, and that these policies may change over time."
msgstr ""
"Standardi kodiranja QGIS-a opisani su u dokumentu o politikama dostupnom na "
"adresi `QEP #314 <https://github.com/qgis/QGIS-Enhancement-"
"Proposals/blob/master/qep-314-coding-style.md>`_. Svi programeri su dužni da"
" se pridržavaju tih politika. Imajte u vidu da je QEP #314 aktivni dokument "
"i da se ove politike mogu menjati tokom vremena."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:15
msgid "Classes"
msgstr "Časovi"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:19
msgid "Accessor Functions"
msgstr "Funkcije pristupnika"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:21
msgid ""
"Ensure that accessors are correctly marked with ``const``. Where "
"appropriate, this may require that cached value type member variables are "
"marked with ``mutable``."
msgstr ""
"Uverite se da su pristupnici pravilno označeni sa „const“. Gde je to "
"potrebno, ovo može zahtevati da keširane promenljive članice tipa vrednosti "
"budu označene sa „mutable“."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:27
msgid "Function Arguments"
msgstr "Argumenti funkcije"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:29
msgid ""
"Pay careful attention to when arguments should be passed by reference. "
"Unless argument objects are small and trivially copied (such as QPoint "
"objects), they should be passed by const reference. For consistency with the"
" Qt API, even implicitly shared objects are passed by const reference (e.g. "
"``setTitle( const QString& title )`` instead of ``setTitle( QString title "
")``."
msgstr ""
"Obratite pažnju kada argumente treba prosleđivati referencom. Osim ako "
"objekti argumenata nisu mali i trivijalno se kopiraju (kao što su QPoint "
"objekti), treba ih prosleđivati konstantnom referencom. Radi doslednosti sa "
"Qt API-jem, čak se i implicitno deljeni objekti prosleđuju konstantnom "
"referencom (npr. ``setTitle( const QString& title )`` umesto ``setTitle( "
"QString title )``."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:38
msgid "Function Return Values"
msgstr "Vrednosti koje vraća funkcija"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:40
msgid ""
"Return small and trivially copied objects as values. Larger objects should "
"be returned by const reference. The one exception to this is implicitly "
"shared objects, which are always returned by value. Return ``QObject`` or "
"subclassed objects as pointers."
msgstr ""
"Vraćajte male i trivijalno kopirane objekte kao vrednosti. Veće objekte "
"treba vraćati konstantnom referencom. Jedini izuzetak od ovoga su implicitno"
" deljeni objekti, koji se uvek vraćaju kao vrednost. Vraćajte ``QObject`` "
"ili izvedene objekte kao pokazivače."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:45
msgid "``int maximumValue() const``"
msgstr "``int maximumValue() const``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:46
msgid "``const LayerSet& layers() const``"
msgstr "``const LayerSet& layers() const``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:47
msgid "``QString title() const`` (``QString`` is implicitly shared)"
msgstr "``QString title() const`` (``QString`` je implicitno deljen)"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:48
msgid ""
"``QList< QgsMapLayer* > layers() const`` (``QList`` is implicitly shared)"
msgstr ""
"``QList< QgsMapLayer* > layers() const`` (``QList`` je implicitno deljen)"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:49
msgid ""
"``QgsVectorLayer *layer() const;`` (``QgsVectorLayer`` inherits ``QObject``)"
msgstr ""
"``QgsVectorLayer *layer() const;`` (``QgsVectorLayer`` nasleđuje "
"``QObject``)"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:50
msgid ""
"``QgsAbstractGeometry *geometry() const;`` (``QgsAbstractGeometry`` is "
"abstract and will probably need to be casted)"
msgstr ""
"``QgsAbstractGeometry *geometry() const;`` (``QgsAbstractGeometry`` je "
"apstraktan i verovatno će morati da se kastuje)"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:55
msgid "API Documentation"
msgstr "Dokumentacija API-ja"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:57
msgid ""
"It is required to write API documentation for every class, method, enum and "
"other code that is available in the public API."
msgstr ""
"Obavezno je pisati dokumentaciju API-ja za svaku klasu, metod, nabrajanje i "
"drugi kôd dostupan u javnom API-ju."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:60
msgid ""
"QGIS uses `Doxygen <https://www.doxygen.nl/index.html>`_ for documentation. "
"Write descriptive and meaningful comments that give a reader information "
"about what to expect, what happens in edge cases and give hints about other "
"interfaces he could be looking for, best practices and code samples."
msgstr ""
"QGIS koristi `Doxygen <https://www.doxygen.nl/index.html>`_ za "
"dokumentaciju. Pišite opisne i smislene komentare koji čitaocu daju "
"informacije o tome šta da očekuje, šta se dešava u graničnim slučajevima i "
"daju nagoveštaje o drugim interfejsima koje bi mogao tražiti, o najboljim "
"praksama i primerima koda."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:67
msgid "Members Variables"
msgstr "Promenljive članice"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:69
msgid ""
"Member variables should normally be in the ``private`` section and made "
"available via getters and setters. One exception to this is for data "
"containers like for error reporting. In such cases do not prefix the member "
"with an ``m``."
msgstr ""
"Promenljive članice obično treba da budu u ``private`` odeljku i dostupne "
"preko getera i setera. Jedan izuzetak od ovoga su kontejneri podataka, kao "
"za prijavljivanje grešaka. U takvim slučajevima nemojte članu dodavati "
"prefiks ``m``."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:75
msgid "Qt Designer"
msgstr "Qt Designer"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:78
msgid "Generated Classes"
msgstr "Generisane klase"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:80
msgid ""
"QGIS classes that are generated from Qt Designer (ui) files should have a "
"Base suffix. This identifies the class as a generated base class."
msgstr ""
"QGIS klase generisane iz Qt Designer (ui) datoteka treba da imaju sufiks "
"Base. Time se klasa identifikuje kao generisana bazna klasa."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:83
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr "Primeri:"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:85
msgid "``QgsPluginManagerBase``"
msgstr "``QgsPluginManagerBase``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:86
msgid "``QgsUserOptionsBase``"
msgstr "``QgsUserOptionsBase``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:90
msgid "Dialogs"
msgstr "Dijalozi"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:92
msgid ""
"All dialogs should implement tooltip help for all toolbar icons and other "
"relevant widgets. Tooltips add greatly to feature discoverability for both "
"new and experienced users."
msgstr ""
"Svi dijalozi treba da implementiraju pomoć u vidu iskačuće pomoći za sve "
"ikone palete alatki i druge relevantne vidžete. Iskačuća pomoć znatno "
"doprinosi otkrivljivosti mogućnosti kako za nove tako i za iskusne "
"korisnike."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:96
msgid ""
"Ensure that the tab order for widgets is updated whenever the layout of a "
"dialog changes."
msgstr ""
"Uverite se da se redosled tabulacije za vidžete ažurira svaki put kada se "
"raspored dijaloga promeni."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:101
msgid "C++ Files"
msgstr "C++ datoteke"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:104
msgid "Standard Header and License"
msgstr "Standardno zaglavlje i licenca"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:106
msgid ""
"Each source file should contain a header section patterned after the "
"following example:"
msgstr ""
"Svaka izvorna datoteka treba da sadrži odeljak zaglavlja po uzoru na sledeći"
" primer:"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:126
msgid ""
"There is a template for Qt Creator in git repository. To use it, copy it "
"from :source:`qt_creator_license_template "
"<editors/QtCreator/qt_creator_license_template>` to a local location, adjust"
" the mail address and - if required - the name and configure QtCreator to "
"use it: :menuselection:`Tools --> Options --> C++ --> File Naming`."
msgstr ""
"U git repozitorijumu postoji šablon za Qt Creator. Da biste ga koristili, "
"kopirajte ga iz :source:`qt_creator_license_template "
"<editors/QtCreator/qt_creator_license_template>` na lokalnu lokaciju, "
"prilagodite adresu e-pošte i - ako je potrebno - ime i konfigurišite "
"QtCreator da ga koristi: :menuselection:`Tools --> Options --> C++ --> File "
"Naming`."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:133
msgid "Editing"
msgstr "Uređivanje"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:135
msgid ""
"Any text editor/IDE can be used to edit QGIS code, providing the following "
"requirements are met."
msgstr ""
"Za uređivanje QGIS koda može se koristiti bilo koji tekstualni uređivač/IDE,"
" pod uslovom da su ispunjeni sledeći zahtevi."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:139
msgid "Tabs"
msgstr "Tabulatori"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:141
msgid ""
"Set your editor to emulate tabs with spaces. Tab spacing should be set to 2 "
"spaces."
msgstr ""
"Podesite svoj uređivač da emulira tabulatore razmacima. Razmak tabulatora "
"treba postaviti na 2 razmaka."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:144
msgid "In vim this is done with ``set expandtab ts=2``"
msgstr "U vim-u se to radi pomoću ``set expandtab ts=2``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:147
msgid "Indentation"
msgstr "Uvlačenje"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:149
msgid ""
"Source code should be indented to improve readability. There is a "
":source:`prepare_commit.sh <scripts/prepare_commit.sh>` file that looks up "
"the changed files and reindents them using astyle. This should be run before"
" committing. You can also use :source:`astyle.sh <scripts/astyle.sh>` to "
"indent individual files."
msgstr ""
"Izvorni kôd treba uvlačiti radi bolje čitljivosti. Postoji datoteka "
":source:`prepare_commit.sh <scripts/prepare_commit.sh>` koja pronalazi "
"izmenjene datoteke i ponovo ih uvlači pomoću astyle. Ovo treba pokrenuti pre"
" komitovanja. Za uvlačenje pojedinačnih datoteka možete koristiti i "
":source:`astyle.sh <scripts/astyle.sh>`."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:155
msgid ""
"As newer versions of astyle indent differently than the version used to do a"
" complete reindentation of the source, the script uses an old astyle "
"version, that we include in our repository (enable ``WITH_ASTYLE`` in cmake "
"to include it in the build)."
msgstr ""
"Pošto novije verzije astyle uvlače drugačije od verzije korišćene za potpuno"
" ponovno uvlačenje izvornog koda, skripta koristi staru verziju astyle, koju"
" uključujemo u naš repozitorijum (omogućite ``WITH_ASTYLE`` u cmake da biste"
" ga uključili u build)."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:162
msgid "API Compatibility"
msgstr "Kompatibilnost API-ja"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:164
msgid "There is :api:`API documentation <>` for C++."
msgstr "Postoji :api:`dokumentacija API-ja <>` za C++."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:166
msgid ""
"We try to keep the API stable and backwards compatible. Cleanups to the API "
"should be done in a manner similar to the Qt source code e.g."
msgstr ""
"Trudimo se da API bude stabilan i unazad kompatibilan. Čišćenja API-ja treba"
" raditi na način sličan Qt izvornom kodu, npr."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:206
msgid "SIP Bindings"
msgstr "SIP vezivanja"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:208
msgid ""
"Some of the SIP files are automatically generated using a dedicated script."
msgstr "Neke SIP datoteke se automatski generišu pomoću posebne skripte."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:212
msgid "Header pre-processing"
msgstr "Predobrada zaglavlja"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:215
msgid ""
"All the information to properly build the SIP file must be found in the C++ "
"header file. Some macros are available for such definition:"
msgstr ""
"Sve informacije za ispravno pravljenje SIP datoteke moraju se nalaziti u C++"
" datoteci zaglavlja. Za takvu definiciju dostupno je nekoliko makroa:"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:218
msgid ""
"Use ``#ifdef SIP_RUN`` to generate code only in SIP files or ``#ifndef "
"SIP_RUN`` for C++ code only. ``#else`` statements are handled in both cases."
msgstr ""
"Koristite ``#ifdef SIP_RUN`` za generisanje koda samo u SIP datotekama ili "
"``#ifndef SIP_RUN`` samo za C++ kôd. Naredbe ``#else`` se rukuju u oba "
"slučaja."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:221
msgid "Use ``SIP_SKIP`` to discard a line"
msgstr "Koristite ``SIP_SKIP`` da biste odbacili liniju"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:222
msgid "The following annotations are handled:"
msgstr "Sledeće anotacije se rukuju:"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:224
msgid "``SIP_FACTORY``: ``/Factory/``"
msgstr "``SIP_FACTORY``: ``/Factory/``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:225
msgid "``SIP_OUT``: ``/Out/``"
msgstr "``SIP_OUT``: ``/Out/``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:226
msgid "``SIP_INOUT``: ``/In,Out/``"
msgstr "``SIP_INOUT``: ``/In,Out/``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:227
msgid "``SIP_TRANSFER``: ``/Transfer/``"
msgstr "``SIP_TRANSFER``: ``/Transfer/``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:228
msgid "``SIP_PYNAME(name)``: ``/PyName=name/``"
msgstr "``SIP_PYNAME(name)``: ``/PyName=name/``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:229
msgid "``SIP_KEEPREFERENCE``: ``/KeepReference/``"
msgstr "``SIP_KEEPREFERENCE``: ``/KeepReference/``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:230
msgid "``SIP_TRANSFERTHIS``: ``/TransferThis/``"
msgstr "``SIP_TRANSFERTHIS``: ``/TransferThis/``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:231
msgid "``SIP_TRANSFERBACK``: ``/TransferBack/``"
msgstr "``SIP_TRANSFERBACK``: ``/TransferBack/``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:233
msgid ""
"``private`` sections are not displayed, except if you use a ``#ifdef "
"SIP_RUN`` statement in this block."
msgstr ""
"``private`` odeljci se ne prikazuju, osim ako u tom bloku koristite naredbu "
"``#ifdef SIP_RUN``."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:235
msgid ""
"``SIP_PYDEFAULTVALUE(value)`` can be used to define an alternative default "
"value of the python method. If the default value contains a comma ``,``, the"
" value should be surrounded by single quotes ``'``"
msgstr ""
"``SIP_PYDEFAULTVALUE(value)`` može se koristiti za definisanje alternativne "
"podrazumevane vrednosti python metoda. Ako podrazumevana vrednost sadrži "
"zarez ``,``, vrednost treba okružiti jednostrukim navodnicima ``'``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:238
msgid ""
"``SIP_PYTYPE(type)`` can be used to define an alternative type for an "
"argument of the python method. If the type contains a comma ``,``, the type "
"should be surrounded by single quotes ``'``"
msgstr ""
"``SIP_PYTYPE(type)`` može se koristiti za definisanje alternativnog tipa za "
"argument python metoda. Ako tip sadrži zarez ``,``, tip treba okružiti "
"jednostrukim navodnicima ``'``"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:242
msgid ""
"A demo file, :source:`sipifyheader.h "
"<tests/code_layout/sipify/sipifyheader.h>`, is also available."
msgstr ""
"Dostupna je i demo datoteka, :source:`sipifyheader.h "
"<tests/code_layout/sipify/sipifyheader.h>`."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:246
msgid "Generating the SIP file"
msgstr "Generisanje SIP datoteke"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:248
msgid "The SIP file can be generated using a dedicated script. For instance:"
msgstr "SIP datoteka se može generisati pomoću posebne skripte. Na primer:"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:254
msgid ""
"To automatically generate the SIP file of a newly added C++ file "
":source:`sip_include.sh <scripts/sip_include.sh>` needs to be executed."
msgstr ""
"Za automatsko generisanje SIP datoteke novododate C++ datoteke potrebno je "
"izvršiti :source:`sip_include.sh <scripts/sip_include.sh>`."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:257
msgid ""
"As soon as a SIP file is added to one of the source file "
"(:source:`core_auto.sip <python/core/core_auto.sip>`, :source:`gui_auto.sip "
"<python/gui/gui_auto.sip>` or :source:`analysis_auto.sip "
"<python/analysis/analysis_auto.sip>`), it will be considered as generated "
"automatically. A test will ensure that this file is up to date with its "
"corresponding header."
msgstr ""
"Čim se SIP datoteka doda u jednu od izvornih datoteka "
"(:source:`core_auto.sip <python/core/core_auto.sip>`, :source:`gui_auto.sip "
"<python/gui/gui_auto.sip>` ili :source:`analysis_auto.sip "
"<python/analysis/analysis_auto.sip>`), smatraće se automatski generisanom. "
"Test će obezbediti da ova datoteka bude ažurna sa svojim odgovarajućim "
"zaglavljem."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:264
msgid ""
"To force recreation of SIP files, :source:`sipify_all.sh "
"<scripts/sipify_all.sh>` shall be executed."
msgstr ""
"Da biste prisilili ponovno pravljenje SIP datoteka, treba izvršiti "
":source:`sipify_all.sh <scripts/sipify_all.sh>`."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:268
msgid "Improving sipify script"
msgstr "Poboljšanje sipify skripte"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:270
msgid ""
"If some improvements are required for sipify script, please add the missing "
"bits to the demo file :source:`sipifyheader.h "
"<tests/code_layout/sipify/sipifyheader.h>` and create the expected header "
":file:`sipifyheader.expected.sip` file. This will also be automatically "
"tested as a unit test of the script itself."
msgstr ""
"Ako su za sipify skriptu potrebna neka poboljšanja, dodajte delove koji "
"nedostaju u demo datoteku :source:`sipifyheader.h "
"<tests/code_layout/sipify/sipifyheader.h>` i napravite očekivanu datoteku "
"zaglavlja :file:`sipifyheader.expected.sip`. I ovo će biti automatski "
"testirano kao jedinični test same skripte."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:277
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "Podešavanja"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:279
msgid ""
"QGIS code base offers a mechanism to declare, register and use settings."
msgstr ""
"QGIS kodna baza nudi mehanizam za deklarisanje, registrovanje i korišćenje "
"podešavanja."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:281
msgid ""
"settings should be defined using one of the available implementations "
"(:api:`QgsSettingsEntryString <classQgsSettingsEntryString.html>`, "
":api:`QgsSettingsEntryInteger <classQgsSettingsEntryInteger.html>`, …)."
msgstr ""
"podešavanja treba definisati pomoću jedne od dostupnih implementacija "
"(:api:`QgsSettingsEntryString <classQgsSettingsEntryString.html>`, "
":api:`QgsSettingsEntryInteger <classQgsSettingsEntryInteger.html>`, …)."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:284
msgid ""
"settings must be integrated in the settings tree (:api:`QgsSettingsTree "
"<classQgsSettingsTree.html>`), this is automatically done when using the "
"constructor with a parent node (:api:`QgsSettingsTreeNode "
"<classQgsSettingsTreeNode.html>`)."
msgstr ""
"podešavanja moraju biti integrisana u stablo podešavanja "
"(:api:`QgsSettingsTree <classQgsSettingsTree.html>`); ovo se automatski radi"
" pri korišćenju konstruktora sa nadređenim čvorom (:api:`QgsSettingsTreeNode"
" <classQgsSettingsTreeNode.html>`)."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:287
msgid ""
"they are declared as ``const static`` either in a dedicated class or in the "
"registry directly (core, gui, app, …)."
msgstr ""
"deklarišu se kao ``const static`` bilo u posebnoj klasi ili direktno u "
"registru (core, gui, app, …)."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:289
msgid "the setting key should be using a ``kebab-case``."
msgstr "ključ podešavanja treba da koristi ``kebab-case``."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:292
msgid "Coding Style"
msgstr "Stil kodiranja"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:295
msgid ""
"Here are described some programming hints and tips that will hopefully "
"reduce errors, development time and maintenance."
msgstr ""
"Ovde su opisani neki saveti i trikovi za programiranje koji će, nadamo se, "
"smanjiti greške, vreme razvoja i održavanje."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:300
msgid "Where-ever Possible Generalize Code"
msgstr "Gde god je moguće, generalizujte kôd"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:302
msgid ""
"If you are cut-n-pasting code, or otherwise writing the same thing more than"
" once, consider consolidating the code into a single function."
msgstr ""
"Ako sečete i lepite kôd, ili na drugi način pišete istu stvar više puta, "
"razmotrite objedinjavanje koda u jednu funkciju."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:305
msgid "This will:"
msgstr "Ovo će:"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:307
msgid "allow changes to be made in one location instead of in multiple places"
msgstr "omogućiti da se izmene naprave na jednom mestu umesto na više mesta"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:308
msgid "help prevent code bloat"
msgstr "pomoći u sprečavanju bujanja koda"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:309
msgid ""
"make it more difficult for multiple copies to evolve differences over time, "
"thus making it harder to understand and maintain for others"
msgstr ""
"otežati da više kopija tokom vremena razvije razlike, čime se drugima "
"otežava razumevanje i održavanje"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:314
msgid "Put commands on separate lines"
msgstr "Stavljajte komande u zasebne linije"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:316
msgid ""
"When reading code it's easy to miss commands, if they are not at the "
"beginning of the line. When quickly reading through code, it's common to "
"skip lines if they don't look like what you are looking for in the first few"
" characters. It's also common to expect a command after a conditional like "
"``if``."
msgstr ""
"Pri čitanju koda lako je propustiti komande ako nisu na početku linije. Pri "
"brzom čitanju koda uobičajeno je preskočiti linije ako u prvih nekoliko "
"znakova ne izgledaju kao ono što tražite. Takođe je uobičajeno očekivati "
"komandu posle uslova kao što je ``if``."

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:321
msgid "Consider:"
msgstr "Razmotrite:"

#: ../../docs/developers_guide/codingstandards.rst:329
